# Artillery ERP — Environment Variables

Copy to `.env.local` for local development.

```env
# ── Data provider ──────────────────────────────────────────────
# "supabase" (default) or "api" (self-hosted VPS backend)
NEXT_PUBLIC_DATA_PROVIDER=supabase

# Required when NEXT_PUBLIC_DATA_PROVIDER=api
NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL=http://localhost:4000

# ── Supabase (default provider) ────────────────────────────────
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project.supabase.co
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your_anon_key

# Server-side only — never expose to the browser
SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=your_service_role_key

# ── Backend API (backend/.env) ─────────────────────────────────
# DATABASE_URL=postgresql://artillery_app:password@localhost:5432/artillery_erp
# JWT_SECRET=generate-with-openssl-rand-base64-48
# PORT=4000
# CORS_ORIGINS=http://localhost:3000,https://artilleryerp.vercel.app
```

## Local dual-stack testing

Terminal 1 — API (point `DATABASE_URL` at Supabase pooler or local Postgres):

```bash
cd backend && cp .env.example .env && npm run dev
```

Terminal 2 — Frontend with API provider:

```bash
# .env.local
NEXT_PUBLIC_DATA_PROVIDER=api
NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL=http://localhost:4000

npm run dev
```

Or run both: `npm run dev:api` in one terminal and `npm run dev` in another.
